<entry dateCreated="2005-06-23T16:30:30Z" dateModified="2006-09-05T17:58:33Z" id="adidi_a15b8ae6-207c-4999-b1e0-f95a348d1bdc" guid="a15b8ae6-207c-4999-b1e0-f95a348d1bdc">
<lexical-unit>
<form lang="seh"><text>adidi</text></form>
</lexical-unit>
<trait  name="morph-type" value="root"/>
<sense id="892fa71e-e2cb-4e2f-9ca9-d37d77c5acda" order="0">
<grammatical-info value="Adjectivo">
</grammatical-info>
<gloss lang="en"><text>good</text></gloss>
<gloss lang="pt"><text>bom</text></gloss>
<example>
<form lang="seh"><text>akazi adidi</text></form>
<translation type="Free translation">
<form lang="pt"><text>boas mulheres</text></form>
</translation>
</example>
<note type="grammar">
<form lang="en"><text>Question: m'phyadidi = ndi + pyadidi Note that N made it become aspirated.; Question: There are a lot of ndi + fusions eg: nduwo=ndi+uwo, m'khufa ndi+kufa</text></form>
</note>
<field type="Parsing Note">
<form lang="en"><text>Is the root adidi or didi?; adj0 put in to handle "adidi" form</text></form>
</field>
</sense>
<sense id="13e26eb7-5809-40d3-a08d-78c704ba8a30" order="1">
<grammatical-info value="Nome">
</grammatical-info>
<gloss lang="en"><text>right side</text></gloss>
<gloss lang="pt"><text>direita</text></gloss>
</sense>
</entry>
<entry dateCreated="2005-06-23T16:30:30Z" dateModified="2006-09-06T16:11:57Z" id="bambaya_03d6652b-0af8-40a3-b2ee-574c53dcfb2c" guid="03d6652b-0af8-40a3-b2ee-574c53dcfb2c">
<lexical-unit>
<form lang="seh"><text>bambaya</text></form>
</lexical-unit>
<trait  name="morph-type" value="root"/>
<field type="Plural">
<form lang="seh"><text>mabambaya</text></form>
</field>
<sense id="d59756d9-3fe2-4cd6-9e2e-372ae603152a">
<grammatical-info value="Nome">
<trait name="inflection-feature" value="{Infl}[NounAgr:[genro:14/6]]"/>
</grammatical-info>
<gloss lang="en"><text>sweet potato</text></gloss>
<gloss lang="pt"><text>batata doce</text></gloss>
<example source="Nyazeze">
<form lang="seh"><text>mabambaya mikulu</text></form>
<translation type="Free translation">
<form lang="pt"><text>batata doce grande</text></form>
</translation>
<note type="reference">
<form lang="en"><text>Nyazeze</text></form>
</note>
</example>
<note>
<form lang="en"><text>Question: Why is this class 6 using mi- for it's concord? Could it be the plant?; bambaya wa cizungu = batata reino (white potato)</text></form>
</note>
</sense>
</entry>
